<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="21" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="22.[192,1069,1274,1301]" box="[192,1069,1274,1301]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,348,1274,1300]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Distribution.</emphasis>
Coastal 
<collectingRegion box="[446,562,1274,1300]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">California</collectingRegion>
beaches (Sonoma, Marin, Ventura counties).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[192,1441,1316,1443]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,372,1316,1342]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Larval ecology.</emphasis>
Larvae have been collected from 
<quantity box="[760,845,1316,1342]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="2.0">2–8 cm</quantity>
deep in moist to saturated brackish sandy soil with 640 ppm chloride within a zone occasionally inundated by high tides (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith LM &amp; Lowe H." box="[1007,1260,1349,1376]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" pagination="157 - 183" refId="ref140641" refString="Smith LM, Lowe H. 1948. The black gnats of California. Hilgardia 18: 157 - 183." type="journal article" year="1948">
<collectingRegion box="[1007,1076,1349,1375]" country="Bermuda" name="Smith's" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Smith</collectingRegion>
and Lowe 1948
</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1306,1425,1349,1376]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerteszi">
<emphasis box="[1306,1324,1350,1375]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1340,1425,1349,1375]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">kerteszi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). They found eggs June–August and determined it takes the larvae 8–10 months to mature and then pupate March–August of the following year.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[192,1440,1458,1518]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,375,1458,1484]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Adult behavior.</emphasis>
Males have been collected swarming on the downwind side of objects near shore March–October, and females have been observed to bite humans, dogs, and cats (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith LM &amp; Lowe H." box="[960,1207,1492,1518]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" pagination="157 - 183" refId="ref140641" refString="Smith LM, Lowe H. 1948. The black gnats of California. Hilgardia 18: 157 - 183." type="journal article" year="1948">
<collectingRegion box="[960,1029,1492,1518]" country="Bermuda" name="Smith's" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Smith</collectingRegion>
and Lowe 1948
</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1247,1365,1492,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kerteszi">
<emphasis box="[1247,1267,1492,1517]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1280,1365,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">kerteszi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[192,1109,1533,1560]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[192,1109,1533,1560]" box="[192,1109,1533,1560]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,304,1533,1559]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the infamous Bodega black gnat. No 
<taxonomicName box="[805,924,1533,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Leptoconops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arnaudi">
<emphasis box="[805,820,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[833,924,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">arnaudi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were examined.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
